<subSubSection id="93BF6564B94C4026FF0EFC10FA8012D8" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DB1A36EFB94C4026FF0EFC10FBB0119B" blockId="5.[136,1452,881,1155]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94C4026FF0EFC10FE9316EB" bold="true" box="[136,267,989,1011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Diagnosis:—</emphasis>
The erect habit and peltate leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94C4026FDE8FC13FCA016EA" authorityName="Ardi, Girm. &amp; Randi. A. Habit" authorityYear="2022" box="[622,824,989,1011]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sangkulirangensis">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94C4026FDE8FC13FCA016EA" box="[622,824,989,1011]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">B. sangkulirangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94C4026FC43FC13FAB616EB" authority="Joffre (2015: 35)" authorityName="Joffre" authorityPageNumber="35" authorityYear="2015" box="[965,1326,989,1011]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nothobaramensis">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94C4026FC43FC13FB1D16EA" box="[965,1157,989,1011]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">B. nothobaramensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BF344B1EB94C4026FB0DFC10FAB616EB" author="Joffre, A. A. &amp; Kiew, R. &amp; Julia, S. &amp; Repin, R." box="[1163,1326,989,1011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" pagination="7 - 50" refId="ref6263" refString="Joffre, A. A., Kiew, R., Julia, S. &amp; Repin, R. (2015) The Begoniaceae of Brunei Darussalam, Borneo, including two new species. Sandakania 20: 7 - 50." type="journal article" year="2015">Joffre (2015: 35)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="A3B2767FB94C4026FAECFC10FA3316EB" box="[1386,1451,989,1011]" name="Brunei" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Brunei</collectingCountry>
but it can be easily distinguished by its shorter (
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FD1FFBCCFD63110F" box="[665,763,1025,1047]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="cm" value="55.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="50.0">50‒60 cm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FCA1FBCCFCEA110F" box="[807,882,1025,1047]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="cm" value="100.0">100 cm</quantity>
) habit, smaller (7–12 × 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FBE4FBCCFB57110F" box="[1122,1231,1025,1047]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="cm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="3.5">3.5–5.5 cm</quantity>
vs. 9.5–18 × 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FADCFBCCFA3D110F" box="[1370,1445,1025,1047]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="cm" value="7.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="5.0">5–9 cm</quantity>
) lamina, more (45‒55 vs. ca. 36) stamens, female inflorescence consistently with a single (vs. two) flower on a shorter (
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FAA5FBE8FA121123" box="[1315,1418,1061,1083]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FF3BFB84FEBE1147" box="[189,294,1097,1119]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="18.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="17.0">17‒20 mm</quantity>
) pedicel, ovary wing shape cuneate (vs. rounded) at the base and apex. 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94C4026FC54FB87FB4F1146" authorityName="Ardi, Girm. &amp; Randi. A. Habit" authorityYear="2022" box="[978,1239,1097,1119]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sangkulirangensis">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94C4026FC54FB87FB4F1146" box="[978,1239,1097,1119]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Begonia sangkulirangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also differs from both 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94C4026FF3BFBA3FEDF119A" authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1928" box="[189,327,1133,1155]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="baramensis">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94C4026FF3BFBA3FEDF119A" box="[189,327,1133,1155]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">B. baramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94C4026FEF3FBA3FDAD119A" authorityName="Joffre" authorityYear="2015" box="[373,565,1133,1155]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nothobaramensis">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94C4026FEF3FBA3FDAD119A" box="[373,565,1133,1155]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">B. nothobaramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a thicker and more succulent leaf lamina.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB1A36EFB94C4026FF0EFB7FFA8012D8" blockId="5.[136,1452,1202,2056]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">
An erect herb, up to ca. 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FE1EFB7FFE4611D4" box="[408,478,1202,1229]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="cm" value="50.0">50 cm</quantity>
tall. Stem branched, nearly glabrous except for moderate microscopic glandular hairs, reddish-brown, internodes 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FE3BFB1BFD8C11E8" box="[445,532,1238,1264]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="cm" value="5.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="2.0">2–9 cm</quantity>
apart. Stipules caducous, glabrous, elliptic, 6–8 × 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FBEFFB1BFB5411E8" box="[1129,1228,1238,1264]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 mm</quantity>
, midrib prominent, margin entire, translucent, apex narrowed into bristle up to 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FCAFFB37FC18100C" box="[809,896,1274,1301]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long; whitish-greenish. Leaves simple, alternate, glabrous; petioles 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FED2FAD3FE3E1020" box="[340,422,1310,1337]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 cm</quantity>
long, concolourous with the stem, terete; lamina peltate, coriaceous, elliptic, 7–12 × 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FAD1FAD3FF351044" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="cm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="3.5">3.5–5.5 cm</quantity>
, asymmetric, apex acuminate, margin subentire, serrate from the middle part upward to the apex, adaxial surface dark green with brownish veins, abaxial surface pale green, veins reddish to brownish; venation palmate-pinnate, primary veins 5–6, actinodromous, secondary veins craspedodromous.Inflorescence protogynous; female inflorescence solitary, one node basal to male inflorescence or further separated, peduncle 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FC77FA63FBC910D0" box="[1009,1105,1454,1481]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3−5 mm</quantity>
long, reddish-green, glabrous, bracteoles minute, hairlike, persistent; upper distal that bearing male inflorescence paniculate, composed of up to 4 simple monochasium with 4–7 flowers, peduncle 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FD41FA3BFCBF1308" box="[711,807,1526,1553]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5–8 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous; bracts stipule-like, persistent, ovate, ca. 4 × 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FF3EF9D7FE8A132C" box="[184,274,1562,1589]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
, translucent, midrib slightly prominent, pale green, glabrous, apex acuminate and narrowed into bristle ca. 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FF37F9F3FF6B1340" box="[177,243,1598,1624]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long; bracteoles persistent, minute. Staminate flower pedicel up to 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FC7EF9F3FBC81340" box="[1016,1104,1598,1625]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
long, whitish-green, glabrous; tepals 2, broadly ovate, 4–6 × 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FE51F9AFFDAD1364" box="[471,565,1634,1661]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
, greenish-red or dull cream, glabrous, margin entire, apex rounded; androecium symmetric with 48–55 yellow stamens, filaments up to ca. 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FCB6F94BFCEB13B8" box="[816,883,1670,1696]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long, fused at the base, anthers ca. 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FA94F94BFAF213B8" box="[1298,1386,1670,1697]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
long, dehiscing through unilaterally positioned slits ca. ½ as long as the anthers. Pistillate flowers: pedicels 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FB72F967FAF513DC" box="[1268,1389,1706,1732]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13 mm</quantity>
long, pale green, glabrous; ovary 3-locular, cylindrical, 16−18 × 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FC9BF903FCE313F0" box="[797,891,1742,1768]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2−3 mm</quantity>
(wings excluded), pale green, glabrous, placentae bilamellate, wings 3, subequal, base cuneate to rounded, apex subcuneate, widest point up to 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FB14F93FFB4B1214" box="[1170,1235,1778,1804]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
(
<superScript id="2CD09BA7B94C4026FB64F93FFB721218" attach="right" box="[1250,1258,1778,1792]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">1</superScript>
/ 
<subScript id="472134AAB94C4026FB74F8C9FB62120A" attach="left" box="[1266,1274,1796,1810]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">3</subScript>
from the apex); tepals 5, glabrous, white tinged with pink and green, unequal, one smaller elliptic, 5−6 × 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FB13F8DBFB611228" box="[1173,1273,1814,1840]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2−3 mm</quantity>
, the four larger ovate, 8–9 × 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FE9EF8F7FE13124C" box="[280,395,1850,1877]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="5.25" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.5">4.5–6 mm</quantity>
, margin entire, apex rounded; style ca. 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FCB8F8F7FC0B124C" box="[830,915,1850,1877]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
long, basally fused, 3-branched, each stylodium bifurcate in the stigmatic region, stigmatic surface a spirally twisted papillose band, orange. Fruit peduncle up to 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FA1BF893FF2C1284" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long; pedicels up to 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FE1AF84FFE721284" box="[412,490,1922,1949]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
long, pendulous and recurved; seed-bearing part cylindrical, 16−19 × 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FB7DF84FFAC11284" box="[1275,1369,1922,1948]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3−4 mm</quantity>
(wings excluded), wing shape as for ovary, widest point up to ca. 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FC95F86BFCCF12D8" box="[787,855,1958,1984]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
. Seeds barrel-shaped, 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94C4026FBD7F86BFB4012D8" box="[1105,1240,1958,1984]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="93BF6564B94C4025FF3BF804FC431212" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="DB1A36EFB94C4026FF3BF804FCEF1D10" blockId="5.[136,1452,1202,2056]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94C4026FF3BF804FEC112FB" bold="true" box="[189,345,1993,2019]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Distribution:</emphasis>
—Endemic to Borneo, so far only known from the 
<typeStatus id="041E884DB94C4026FC27F807FC4912FC" box="[929,977,1994,2020]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">type</typeStatus>
locality in the Sangkulirang-Mangkalihat Limestone Karst Ecosystem, 
<collectingRegion id="1961F80DB94C4026FE56F823FD6F1D10" box="[464,759,2030,2056]" country="Indonesia" name="Kalimantan Timur" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">East Kalimantan Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="A3B2767FB94C4026FC85F823FCEC1D10" box="[771,884,2030,2056]" name="Indonesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="67">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="8FDA6667B94F4025FF0EF9F2FA1D1385" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5973881" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5973881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5973881/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="68" startId="6.[136,229,1599,1621]" targetBox="[167,1424,192,1567]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="DB1A36EFB94F4025FF0EF9F2FA1D1385" blockId="6.[136,1452,1599,1693]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FF0EF9F2FF65134C" bold="true" box="[136,253,1599,1621]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94F4025FE85F98DFCAD134D" authority="Ardi, Girm. &amp; Randi. A. Habit" authorityName="Ardi, Girm. &amp; Randi. A. Habit" authorityYear="2022" box="[259,821,1599,1621]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="6" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sangkulirangensis">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FE85F98DFD90134C" box="[259,520,1599,1621]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">Begonia sangkulirangensis</emphasis>
Ardi, Girm. &amp; Randi. 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FD66F9F2FD60134C" bold="true" box="[736,760,1599,1620]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">A.</emphasis>
Habit
</taxonomicName>
; 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FCB9F9F2FCCD134C" bold="true" box="[831,853,1599,1620]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">B.</emphasis>
Lamina abaxial surface; 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FBC1F9F2FBC6134D" bold="true" box="[1095,1118,1599,1621]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">C.</emphasis>
Stipule; 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FB33F9F2FB54134C" bold="true" box="[1205,1228,1599,1620]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">D.</emphasis>
Male inflorescence; 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FA13F9F2FA34134C" bold="true" box="[1429,1452,1599,1620]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">E.</emphasis>
Female and male inflorescence; 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FE3CF9AEFE541360" bold="true" box="[442,460,1635,1656]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">F.</emphasis>
Male flowers, 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FDDCF9AEFDEB1361" bold="true" box="[602,627,1635,1657]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">G.</emphasis>
Female flower; 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FC8BF9AEFCBE1360" bold="true" box="[781,806,1635,1656]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">H.</emphasis>
Fruit; 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FCE3F9AEFCEC1360" bold="true" box="[869,884,1635,1656]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">I.</emphasis>
Ovary cross section. Scale bars: A: 5 cm, B: 1 cm, C: 1 mm, D: 5 cm, E: 10 mm, F–G: 5 mm, H: 10 mm, I: 1 mm. Photo A: Mark Hughes; B‒I: Wisnu H. Ardi, from cultivated specimen 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FABFF945FAE71384" box="[1337,1407,1671,1693]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">WI 684</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="DB1A36EFB94F4025FF3BF906FC431212" blockId="6.[136,1451,1739,2091]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FF3BF906FEA613FD" bold="true" box="[189,318,1739,1765]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">Habitat:—</emphasis>
This species was found on a limestone cliff in a shallow cave in deep shade beneath scrubby karst vegetation. It was growing in thin dusty soil on a slightly damp mossy rock.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="93BF6564B94F4024FF3BF8D9FE5D1474" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="6" pageNumber="68" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="DB1A36EFB94F4025FF3BF8D9FE13124A" blockId="6.[136,1451,1739,2091]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FF3BF8D9FEFC1236" bold="true" box="[189,356,1812,1838]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The epithet refers to the name of Sangkulirang, the Limestone Karst Mountain Ecosystem where this species was found.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB1A36EFB94F4025FF3BF896FBB11D33" blockId="6.[136,1451,1739,2091]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94F4025FF3BF896FDF1126D" bold="true" box="[189,617,1883,1909]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">Provisional Conservation Status:—</emphasis>
Vulnerable (VU, D2). This species is only known from single collection from the Sangkulirang Mangkalihat Limestone Karst Ecosystem. The area does not yet have legal protected status, and there are clear signs of anthropogenic disturbance (oil palm plantations and mining) around the karst formations. As a karst micro-endemic it therefore is ‘prone to the effects of human activities or stochastic events within a very short time period in an uncertain future’ (
<bibRefCitation id="BF344B1EB94F4025FD92F821FBCC1D1E" author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Subcommittee" box="[532,1108,2028,2054]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68" refId="ref6233" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Committee." type="book" year="2019">IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee 2019</bibRefCitation>
). An ex-situ initiative has been started with plants being cultivated at Kebun Raya Bogor (Bogor Botanic Garden).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB1A36EFB94E4024FF3BFF53FE5D1474" blockId="7.[136,1452,158,364]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FF3BFF53FE9115A0" bold="true" box="[189,265,158,184]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">Notes:</emphasis>
—There are four other caulescent species in 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FC8AFF52FC8515A0" box="[780,797,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B</emphasis>
. sect. 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FCEFFF52FC6215A0" box="[873,1018,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">Petermannia</emphasis>
in Borneo with conspicuously peltate leaves: 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94E4024FF58FF0EFDDA15C4" authority="Sands (1990: 81)" authorityName="Sands" authorityPageNumber="81" authorityYear="1990" box="[222,578,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amphioxus">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FF58FF0EFEEF15C4" box="[222,375,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. amphioxus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BF344B1EB94E4024FEF9FF0FFDDA15C4" author="Sands, M. J. S." box="[383,578,194,220]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" pagination="57 - 85" refId="ref6823" refString="Sands, M. J. S. (1990) Six new Begonias from Sabah. Kew Magazine 7: 57 - 85." type="journal article" year="1990">Sands (1990: 81)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94E4024FDC9FF0EFC4B15C5" authority="Merrill (1928: 529)" authorityName="Merrill" authorityPageNumber="529" authorityYear="1928" box="[591,979,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="baramensis">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FDC9FF0EFD6815C4" box="[591,752,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. baramensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BF344B1EB94E4024FD7EFF0FFC4B15C5" author="Merrill, E. D." box="[760,979,194,221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" pagination="513 - 557" refId="ref6590" refString="Merrill, E. D. (1928) A collection of plants from Sarawak. Sarawak Museum Journal 3: 513 - 557." type="journal article" year="1928">Merrill (1928: 529)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94E4024FC5DFF0EFAE315C4" authority="Kiew (2001 b: 272)" authorityName="Kiew" authorityPageNumber="272" authorityYear="2001" box="[987,1403,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="layang-layang">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FC5DFF0EFB0515C4" box="[987,1181,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. layang-layang</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BF344B1EB94E4024FB22FF0FFAE315C4" author="Kiew, R." box="[1188,1403,194,220]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" pagination="241 - 268" refId="ref6414" refString="Kiew, R. (2001 b) The limestone Begonias of Sabah, Borneo - flagship species for conservation. Gardens' Bulletin Singapore 53: 241 - 268." type="journal article" year="2001">Kiew (2001b: 272)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94E4024FF0EFF2AFDA11419" authority="Joffre (2015: 35)" authorityName="Joffre" authorityPageNumber="35" authorityYear="2015" box="[136,569,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nothobaramensis">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FF0EFF2AFEF31418" box="[136,363,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. nothobaramensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BF344B1EB94E4024FEF2FF2BFDA11419" author="Joffre, A. A. &amp; Kiew, R. &amp; Julia, S. &amp; Repin, R." box="[372,569,230,257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" pagination="7 - 50" refId="ref6263" refString="Joffre, A. A., Kiew, R., Julia, S. &amp; Repin, R. (2015) The Begoniaceae of Brunei Darussalam, Borneo, including two new species. Sandakania 20: 7 - 50." type="journal article" year="2015">Joffre (2015: 35)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94E4024FDC1FF2AFCE21418" authorityName="Ardi, Girm. &amp; Randi. A. Habit" authorityYear="2022" box="[583,890,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sangkulirangensis">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FDC1FF2AFCE21418" box="[583,890,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">Begonia sangkulirangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closest to 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94E4024FB92FF2AFB6F1418" authorityName="Joffre" authorityYear="2015" box="[1044,1271,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nothobaramensis">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FB92FF2AFB6F1418" box="[1044,1271,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. nothobaramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as discussed in the diagnosis above, and 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94E4024FE2FFEC6FDD3143C" authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1928" box="[425,587,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="baramensis">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FE2FFEC6FDD3143C" box="[425,587,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. baramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a much larger plant, reaching up to 
<quantity id="1C5D9B0AB94E4024FB8CFEC7FBAF143C" box="[1034,1079,266,292]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" unit="m" value="3.0">3 m</quantity>
tall (
<bibRefCitation id="BF344B1EB94E4024FBF5FEC7FAA2143D" author="Kiew, R. &amp; Sang, J. &amp; Repin, R. &amp; Ahmad, J. A." box="[1139,1338,266,293]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" refId="ref6486" refString="Kiew, R., Sang, J., Repin, R. &amp; Ahmad, J. A. (2015) A Guide to Begonias of Borneo. Natural History Publications (Borneo), Kota Kinabalu. 293 pp." type="book" year="2015">
Kiew 
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FB3CFEC6FB6C143C" box="[1210,1268,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94E4024FAC8FEC6FE991450" authorityName="Sands" authorityYear="1990" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amphioxus">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FAC8FEC6FE991450" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">Begonia amphioxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1CA54D6CB94E4024FEB0FEE2FE6E1450" authorityName="Kiew" authorityYear="2001" box="[310,502,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="layang-layang">
<emphasis id="E9D1EAFDB94E4024FEB0FEE2FE6E1450" box="[310,502,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. layang-layang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not appear to be closely allied, both differing most obviously in their leaves which are acute at the base and tip.
</paragraph>
